    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
            <ab><lb n="1"/><persName><name type="praenomen" key="Lucius"><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan></name> <name type="gentilicium" key="Popillius Popillios">Popillio</name> <name type="cognomen">Flo<gap reason="lost" atLeast="3" unit="character" precision="medium"/></name></persName> 
                <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>fec</abbr><ex>it</ex></expan> <persName><name type="praenomen" key="Lucius"><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan></name> <name type="gentilicium" key="Popillios Popillius">Popillio<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied></name>  
                 <lb n="3"/><name type="cognomen" key="Hadreanus">Hadreanus</name>.</persName> 
            </ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>Lucius Popillios Hadreanus made (this) for Lucius Popillios Flo[rus?].</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Line 1: Many possible completions of <hi rend="italic">Flo-</hi>. Florus is most common by far (~560 in
                    CIL), followed by Florentinus (~220 in CIL). </p>
                    <p>Line 3: <hi rend="italic">Hadreanus</hi> with regular
                    nominative masculine ending, apparently coexisting with Greek ending of
                    <hi rend="italic">Popillios</hi>.</p>
                   <p> Triangular interpuncts between words, none after <hi rend="italic">Hadreanus</hi> in line 3. </p>
            </div>
            

